    <h1 id="how-to-create-storage-resources-using-powershell">How to Create Storage Resources using PowerShell</h1>
    <h3 id="step-by-step-guide-using-powershell">Step-by-step guide using PowerShell</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>
            <strong>Login to Azure account</strong>:
            <code>
                powershell
                Connect-AzAccount
            </code>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Create a new resource group</strong>:
            <code>
                powershell
                New-AzResourceGroup -Name "MyResourceGroup" -Location "EastUS"
            </code>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Create a storage account</strong>:
            <code>
                powershell
                New-AzStorageAccount -ResourceGroupName "MyResourceGroup" -Name "mystorageaccount" -Location "EastUS" -SkuName "Standard_LRS"
            </code>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Create a blob container</strong>:
            <code>
                powershell
                $storageAccount = Get-AzStorageAccount -ResourceGroupName "MyResourceGroup" -Name "mystorageaccount"
                $ctx = $storageAccount.Context
                New-AzStorageContainer -Name "mycontainer" -Context $ctx -Permission Blob
            </code>
        </li>
    </ol>
